item.description:
Here&rsquo;s a regular expression that tests if a string contains at least one uppercase letter, lowercase letter, digit and punctuation/symbol code point, and is at least 8 code points long:
^(?=[\S\s]*?\d)(?=[\S\s]*?\p{Ll})(?=[\S\s]*?\p{Lu})(?=[\S\s]*?[\pP\pS])[\S\s]{8} Equivalent pomsky expression:
Start (&gt;&gt; [cp]* [digit]) (&gt;&gt; [cp]* [Ll]) (&gt;&gt; [cp]* [Lu]) (&gt;&gt; [cp]* [P S]) [cp]{8}
